reviews.text: I seldom give low rating for restaurants, but just because the taste is not leveling up to its cost. I have paid more at other restaurant's dish but the taste will make you forget about the cost, but here you will feel regret for not going to other restaurants that is more satisfying. For instance is their pad thai that tasted like it has mayonnaise.

We had a table of two and ordered a salad and a main of duck and two drinks.
Tuna salad : 2/5 (just a bunch of veggie with some tuna and an egg)
Duck with fried rice: 3/5 (the duck is okay, the rice is tasty but a bit oily)
Service: 1/5 (the server did not know how to serve)
Environment: 3/5 (it was good for talking, quite quiet as not many people)

Overall, I will not come back again.
Nice food and drink. Varied menu Western & Asian. Good service

Here has so much to offer-- from it's staff, to its menu, and let's not forget the delicious coffees. 
Everything is so fresh and delicious--
and there are so many items to select from when you're asked what you'd
like to order. A very relaxing environment. Go and enjoy!!!
Would have given it a higher score if the hostess was not so utterly miserable. Food good, service OK, hostess, spoiled the overall experience...

reviews.text: It's an eye candy. There's a lot of high end brand, so make sure to bring a lot of money. One of the best place to have a shopping spree

The Time Square of Hong Kong, nice ambience with tons of stores! Movie theater, nice big supermarket nearby and a skip away from a wet mart. Literally has everything. They usually do seasonal events at the front which is pretty interesting.
Very popular shopping centre. Great place to spend time
Shopping center in Wan Chai. Not the fanciest of fanciest, but pretty good brands and not too busy.
The age is showing on the exterior, but the stores stay relevant. Still a great place to get all your shopping done.
